import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['rate'])]
    mean_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(mean_rate, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean Rate: {mean_rate:.2f}')
    ax.set_title('What is the average rate in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['rate'], ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['rate'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the range of rate values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
